4 A RESOLUTION OF THE SENATE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA URGING THE UNITED STATES
5 CONGRESS TO CONFIRM BY CONSTITUTIONAL AMENDMENT THE RIGHT TO PROHIBIT CORPORATE
6 CAMPAIGN CONTRIBUTIONS AND EXPENDITURES AND THE RIGHT TO LIMIT POLITICAL SPENDING IN
7 ELECTIONS AND REQUESTING CONGRESS TO SEND THE AMENDMENT TO THE STATES FOR
8 RATIFICATION.
9
10 WHEREAS, government of, by, and for the people is a foundational American value; and
11 WHEREAS, the people of the United States enacted the Constitution of the United States to ensure
12 self-governance and to secure the blessings of liberty; and
13 WHEREAS, free and fair elections are essential to democracy and effective, representative self-
14 governance; and
15 WHEREAS, the United States Congress and state legislatures should have the authority to set
16 reasonable limits and conditions on campaign contributions to ensure effective self-governance; and
17 WHEREAS, in 1912, hardworking Montanans achieved protected elections, after struggling for decades
18 against corruption, when they passed by citizen initiative the Montana Corrupt Practices Act with over 76% of
19 the vote and a majority in every county. For nearly 100 years, the Act prohibited corporate contributions and
20 expenditures and limited those of individuals, until the 2010 U.S. Supreme Court case Citizens United v. FEC,
21 558 U.S. 310 (2010), and following decisions struck down those protections; and
22 WHEREAS, the citizens of Montana are now very concerned about the continued, deepening erosion
23 of our democratic processes by the unlimited, massive expenditures by corporations in our election process
24 and do not accept this attack on our democratic processes; and
25 WHEREAS, out-of-state corporate money used in election campaigns has had a dramatic effect on
26 Montana's elections and on politics across the nation; and
27 WHEREAS, regardless of our political leanings and party affiliations, Montanans see that these
28 influences have overwhelmed our citizens' voices in recent campaigns, have interfered with Montanans' right to
- 1 - LC 656

